#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loans"
msgstr "Posojila"

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "Understanding Loans"
msgstr "Razumevanje posojil"

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid "Feedback requested"
msgstr "Zahtevane povratne informacije"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The author would appreciate feedback on whether to expand this section to "
"discuss the variation of principal and interest to attain a fixed recurring "
"payment. It is mentioned in the section on actually creating a loan in "
"&kmymoney; but it seems it should be mentioned earlier."
msgstr ""
"Avtor bi bil hvaležen za povratne informacije o tem, ali naj ta razdelek "
"razširi na razpravo o variaciji glavnice in obresti za doseganje fiksnega "
"ponavljajočega se plačila. Omenjeno je v razdelku o dejanskem ustvarjanju "
"posojila v &kmymoney; vendar se zdi, da bi bilo treba prej omeniti."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:25
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter describes how &kmymoney; handles loans. Loan regulations and "
"customs vary from locality to locality. For detailed explanations of loans, "
"as well as information on local regulations and customs, please see other "
"resources."
msgstr ""
"To poglavje opisuje, kako &kmymoney; obravnava posojila. Predpisi o "
"posojilih in običaji se razlikujejo od kraja do kraja. Za podrobne razlage "
"posojil ter informacije o lokalnih predpisih in običajih si oglejte druge "
"vire."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A loan is an agreement under which a borrower receives money from a lender "
"and agrees to return the money as one or more repayments in the future. "
"&kmymoney; allows you to track loans by which you, as borrower, receive "
"money from or, as lender, give money to someone else. Most individuals "
"borrow more than they lend, so you will generally be the borrower and a "
"finance company will generally be the lender. If you lend money to a family "
"member or a friend, you can use &kmymoney; to keep track of this loan as "
"well."
msgstr ""
"Posojilo je pogodba, po kateri posojilojemalec prejme denar od "
"posojilodajalca in se strinja, da bo denar vrnil kot eno ali več odplačil v "
"prihodnosti. &kmymoney; omogoča sledenje posojilom, s katerimi kot "
"posojilojemalec prejmete denar ali kot posojilodajalec daste denar nekomu "
"drugemu. Večina posameznikov si več izposoja, kot posoja, zato boste na "
"splošno posojilojemalec vi, posojilodajalec pa bo finančna družba. Če "
"posodite denar družinskemu članu ali prijatelju, lahko uporabite &kmymoney; "
"spremljati tudi to posojilo."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:41
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This guide will assume that you are borrowing from some sort of finance "
"company, but the topics discussed here apply equally well to loans that you "
"might make to a person. The main difference between borrowing and lending "
"money is that an expense category is used to keep track of interest when "
"borrowing money and an income category is used to keep track of interest "
"when lending money."
msgstr ""
"Ta vodnik predvideva, da si izposodite pri nekem finančnem podjetju, vendar "
"teme, obravnavane tukaj, veljajo enako dobro za posojila, ki bi jih lahko "
"dali osebi. Glavna razlika med izposojo in posojo denarja je v tem, da se "
"kategorija odhodkov uporablja za spremljanje obresti pri izposoji denarja, "
"kategorija dohodka pa za spremljanje obresti pri posojanju denarja."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some relevant terms"
msgstr "Nekaj ​​ustreznih izrazov"

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid "Principal"
msgstr "Glavnica"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The amount that is borrowed is called the <quote>principal</quote> or "
"<quote>loan amount</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Znesek, ki je izposojen, se imenuje <quote>glavnica</quote> ali "
"<quote>znesek posojila</quote>."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Term"
msgstr "Izraz"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The period or duration of a loan is called the <quote>term</quote> of the "
"loan. At the end of the term, the entirety of the principal will have been "
"returned to the lender. Terms are generally expressed in weeks, months, or "
"years. A term can also be expressed by the number of payments. For example, "
"a one year loan with weekly repayments could be described as a one year loan "
"or a loan with 52 repayments."
msgstr ""
"Obdobje ali trajanje posojila se imenuje <quote>ročnost</quote> posojila. Ob "
"koncu obdobja bo celotna glavnica vrnjena posojilodajalcu. Pogoji so "
"običajno izraženi v tednih, mesecih ali letih. Rok je lahko izražen tudi s "
"številom plačil. Na primer, enoletno posojilo s tedenskimi odplačili bi "
"lahko opisali kot enoletno posojilo ali posojilo z 52 odplačili."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "Repayments"
msgstr "Odplačila"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The repayment of the principal to the lender is generally not done as a lump "
"sum. Instead, a series of repayments are made, each representing a portion "
"of the principal. Such repayments are sometimes known as <quote>amortization "
"payments</quote> and in &kmymoney; <quote>Amortization</quote> is defined as "
"the act of paying off a loan in installments."
msgstr ""
"Odplačilo glavnice posojilodajalcu se na splošno ne izvede v enkratnem "
"znesku. Namesto tega se izvede niz odplačil, od katerih vsako predstavlja "
"del glavnice. Takšna odplačila so včasih znana kot <quote>amortizacija</"
"quote> in v &kmymoney; <quote>Amortizacija</quote> je opredeljena kot "
"dejanje odplačevanja posojila v obrokih."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "Payment Frequency"
msgstr "Pogostost plačil"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The frequency of installments is referred to as <quote>Payment Frequency</"
"quote>. Examples of this might be weekly, bi-weekly, monthly, quarterly, or "
"yearly. This is also sometimes referred to as the payment period. In the US, "
"periodic payments are most commonly made every month, therefore the loan's "
"period is one month."
msgstr ""
"Pogostost obrokov se imenuje <quote>Pogostost plačil</quote>. Primeri tega "
"so lahko tedenski, dvotedenski, mesečni, četrtletni ali letni. To se včasih "
"imenuje tudi obdobje plačila. V ZDA se periodična plačila najpogosteje "
"izvajajo vsak mesec, zato je obdobje posojila en mesec."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "Interest Rate"
msgstr "Obrestna mera"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For the privilege of being able to use the money, the borrower will pay the "
"lender a fee called the <quote>interest</quote>, normally expressed as a "
"percentage of the amount of the principal over a defined period. Interest "
"rates can be fixed, where the interest rate does not change over the "
"lifetime of the loan, or variable, where the interest rate can change over "
"time. Typically, interest payments are included with each periodic repayment."
msgstr ""
"Za privilegij, da lahko uporablja denar, bo posojilojemalec posojilodajalcu "
"plačal provizijo, imenovano <quote>obresti</quote>, ki je običajno izražena "
"kot odstotek zneska glavnice v določenem obdobju. Obrestne mere so lahko "
"fiksne, kjer se obrestna mera ne spreminja v času trajanja posojila ali "
"spremenljive, kjer se obrestna mera lahko spreminja skozi čas. Običajno so "
"plačila obresti vključena v vsako redno odplačilo."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that a loan in &kmymoney; must have an interest rate greater than 0. "
"Money borrowed or lent with no interest must be entered as a liability or "
"asset account."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da posojilo v &kmymoney; mora imeti obrestno mero, višjo od 0. "
"Denar, izposojen ali posojen brez obresti, je treba vnesti kot konto "
"obveznosti ali imetij."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Periodic Repayments"
msgstr "Periodična odplačila"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since repayments are generally made on some sort of scheduled basis, such as "
"weekly, monthly, quarterly, or yearly, they are referred to as "
"<quote>periodic repayments</quote>. The sum of all periodic repayments plus "
"the final repayment will add up to the loan principal plus the interest."
msgstr ""
"Ker se odplačila običajno izvajajo po nekem načrtu, na primer tedensko, "
"mesečno, četrtletno ali letno, jih imenujemo <quote>periodična odplačila</"
"quote>. Vsota vseh rednih odplačil in končnega odplačila bo seštevek "
"glavnice posojila in obresti."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fees"
msgstr "Pristojbine"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There may be other fees besides interest that are required to be paid, "
"possibly with every installment. These are called <quote>recurring fees</"
"quote>. Examples of recurring fees include (but are not necessarily limited "
"to):"
msgstr ""
"Poleg obresti je morda treba plačati še druge stroške, po možnosti z vsakim "
"obrokom. Te se imenujejo <quote>ponavljajoče se pristojbine</quote>. Primeri "
"ponavljajočih se pristojbin vključujejo (vendar niso nujno omejeni na):"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Impound</quote> or <quote>escrow</quote> account payments. Payments "
"of this sort are commonly used to hold funds to pay annual or bi-annual "
"property taxes."
msgstr ""
"<quote>Zaplemba</quote> ali <quote>deponirana</quote> plačila računa. "
"Plačila te vrste se običajno uporabljajo za hrambo sredstev za plačilo "
"letnih ali polletnih davkov na nepremičnine."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mortgage insurance"
msgstr "Hipotekarno zavarovanje"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disability insurance"
msgstr "Invalidsko zavarovanje"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loan account maintenance fees"
msgstr "Stroški vzdrževanja posojilnega računa"

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Summary"
msgstr "Povzetek"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In summary, the borrower receives a lump sum from the lender at the start of "
"the loan. The borrower makes a periodic payment to the lender. The amount of "
"the periodic payment is the sum of the principal payment (which is used to "
"pay down the balance or remaining principal of the loan,) the interest "
"payment (which rewards the lender for allowing the use of the money by the "
"borrower,) plus any recurring fees (which cover any incidentals.) At the end "
"of the loan, the borrower has paid back the entire principal."
msgstr ""
"Če povzamemo, posojilojemalec na začetku posojila od posojilodajalca prejme "
"pavšalni znesek. Posojilojemalec redno plačuje posojilodajalcu. Znesek "
"rednega plačila je vsota plačila glavnice (ki se uporablja za plačilo "
"preostalega zneska ali preostale glavnice posojila), plačila obresti (ki "
"nagradi posojilodajalca, ker posojilojemalcu dovoli uporabo denarja) plus "
"morebitne ponavljajoče se provizije (ki pokrivajo morebitne nepredvidene "
"stroške). Ob koncu posojila je posojilojemalec vrnil celotno glavnico."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example"
msgstr "Primer"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For an example, you might borrow $25,000.00 for a new automobile and agree "
"to pay the bank one payment each month for 60 months. The interest rate on "
"the loan might be 5.5% per year."
msgstr ""
"Na primer, lahko bi si izposodili 25.000,00 USD za nov avtomobil in se "
"strinjali, da boste banki plačevali eno plačilo vsak mesec 60 mesecev. "
"Obrestna mera za posojilo je lahko 5,5% na leto."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this scenario, the loan amount is $25,000.00. The term of the loan is 60 "
"months or 5 years. The term of the loan could also be described as 60 "
"payments since there will be one payment per month for 5 years. The "
"repayment frequency is one month since periodic repayments will be made once "
"a month. The periodic repayment, which is calculated by &kmymoney;, would be "
"$477.53."
msgstr ""
"V tem scenariju je znesek posojila 25.000,00 USD. Ročnost posojila je 60 "
"mesecev ali 5 let. Trajanje posojila bi lahko opisali tudi kot 60 plačil, "
"saj bo po eno plačilo na mesec v času 5 let. Frekvenca odplačevanja je en "
"mesec, saj bodo periodična odplačila enkrat mesečno. Periodično odplačilo, "
"ki ga izračuna &kmymoney;, bi znašalo 477,53 USD."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <quote>loan schedule</quote> is a chart or table that shows the date that "
"a repayment should be made and the amount of each periodic repayment. Often, "
"these schedules break the periodic payment down into its constituent parts: "
"the principal repayment, the interest payment, and the recurring fees "
"payment."
msgstr ""
"<quote>Razpored posojil</quote> je grafikon ali tabela, ki prikazuje datum, "
"ko je treba opraviti odplačilo, in znesek vsakega rednega odplačila. Ti "
"razporedi pogosto razdelijo periodično plačilo na njegove sestavne dele: "
"odplačilo glavnice, plačilo obresti in plačilo ponavljajočih se nadomestil."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a New Loan"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje novega posojila"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &kmymoney;, a loan is a type of account. Therefore, to create a new loan, "
"you begin by selecting the <menuchoice><guimenu>Account</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>New Account</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. "
"Continue by answering the questions that the wizard poses to you."
msgstr ""
"V &kmymoney; je posojilo vrsta računa. Če želite torej ustvariti novo "
"posojilo, začnete z izbiro menijske postavke <menuchoice><guimenu>Račun</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Nov račun</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Nadaljujte z "
"odgovori na vprašanja, ki vam jih zastavi čarovnik."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>New Account Setup</guilabel> wizard not only sets up a Loan "
"Account, but also creates a <guilabel>Scheduled Transaction</guilabel> for "
"the periodic payments. If you try to edit either the Loan Account or the "
"associated Scheduled Transaction, you will be presented with the "
"<guilabel>Edit Loan Account Wizard</guilabel>. This allows you to adjust "
"many of the details of the loans, but not all. Unfortunately, some aspects "
"of the Loan Account cannot currently be changed, such as the account's "
"parent account."
msgstr ""
"Čarovnik za <guilabel>Nastavitev novega računa</guilabel> ne samo nastavi "
"posojilni račun, ampak ustvari tudi <guilabel>Načrtovano transakcijo</"
"guilabel> za periodična plačila. Če poskušate urediti račun posojila ali "
"povezano načrtovano transakcijo, se vam prikaže <guilabel>čarovnik za "
"urejanje računa posojila</guilabel>. To vam omogoča, da prilagodite številne "
"podrobnosti posojil, vendar ne vseh. Na žalost nekaterih vidikov posojilnega "
"računa trenutno ni mogoče spremeniti, na primer nadrejenega računa tega "
"računa."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you display the <link linkend=\"details.schedules\">Schedules View</"
"link>, right-click on any of the listed schedules, and select "
"<guimenuitem>Edit scheduled transaction</guimenuitem> from the menu which "
"pops up, &kmymoney; will display the <guilabel>Edit scheduled transaction</"
"guilabel> dialog. In contrast, if you do this with a loan schedule, you will "
"be shown the <guilabel>Edit Loan Account Wizard</guilabel>, and mentioned "
"above. However, if you hold down the <keycap>&Shift;</keycap> key when you "
"click <guimenuitem>Edit scheduled transaction</guimenuitem>, the "
"<guilabel>Edit scheduled transaction</guilabel> dialog for the loan will be "
"show, where you can change some of the details of the recurring transaction."
msgstr ""
"Če prikažete <link linkend=\"details.schedules\">Pogled časovnih planov</"
"link>, z desno miškino tipko kliknite katerega koli od navedenih planov in "
"izberite <guimenuitem>Uredi načrtovano transakcijo</guimenuitem> v pojavnem "
"meniju, &kmymoney; prikaže pogovorno okno <guilabel>Uredi načrtovano "
"transakcijo</guilabel>. V nasprotju s tem, če to storite s planom posojil, "
"se vam bo prikazal <guilabel>Čarovnik za urejanje posojilnega računa</"
"guilabel>, ki je omenjen zgoraj. Vendar, če držite tipko <keycap>&Shift;</"
"keycap>, ko kliknete <guimenuitem>Urejanje načrtovane transakcije</"
"guimenuitem>, se prikaže pogovorno okno <guilabel>Urejanje načrtovane "
"transakcije</guilabel> za posojilo, kjer lahko spremenite nekatere "
"podrobnosti ponavljajoče se transakcije."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:208
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Also note that if you delete the schedule associated with a loan, you cannot "
"undo this action, and will have to start from scratch, creating a new loan "
"account and schedule."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte tudi, da če izbrišete časovni plan, povezan s posojilom, tega "
"dejanja ne morete razveljaviti in boste morali začeti iz nič, ustvariti nov "
"račun posojila in časovni plan."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optionally, as with any other account, a loan can be associated with a "
"particular institution. If you are borrowing from a mortgage company or a "
"car loan company, you could create an institution that describes this firm "
"and associate your loan with the institution. If you are borrowing from your "
"Uncle Ted, there is no need to set up an institution."
msgstr ""
"Po želji se lahko, tako kot pri vsakem drugem računu, posojilo poveže z "
"določeno institucijo. Če si najemate posojilo pri hipotekarnem podjetju ali "
"podjetju za izposojo avtomobilov, lahko ustvarite institucijo, ki opisuje to "
"podjetje, in svoje posojilo povežete z institucijo. Če si sposodite pri "
"stricu Tedu, ni treba ustanavljati institucije."

#. Tag: title
#: details-loans.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid "Making Extra Principle Repayments On Loans"
msgstr "Dodatna osnovna odplačila posojil"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you would like to make an extra principal repayment, you can do so. "
"Simply <link linkend=\"details.ledger.transactions\">enter a transaction</"
"link> using the ledger. This extra repayment of principal will be taken into "
"account for the interest calculation that happens for the next periodic "
"payment."
msgstr ""
"Če želite dodatno odplačati glavnico, lahko to storite. Preprosto <link "
"linkend=\"details.ledger.transactions\">vnesite transakcijo</link> z uporabo "
"glavne knjige. To dodatno odplačilo glavnice se bo upoštevalo pri izračunu "
"obresti, ki se izvede za naslednje periodično plačilo."

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Examples of extra principal payments include (but are not necessarily "
"limited to):"
msgstr ""
"Primeri dodatnih plačil glavnice vključujejo (vendar niso nujno omejeni na):"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Contributing an extra $50 a month"
msgstr "Prispevek dodatnih 50 $ na mesec"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Doubling the periodic principal repayment for every period. (The principal "
"repayment can be found for any particular period by referring to the loan "
"schedule.)"
msgstr ""
"Podvojitev rednega odplačevanja glavnice za vsako obdobje. (Odplačilo "
"glavnice je mogoče najti za katero koli določeno obdobje s sklicevanjem na "
"načrt posojila.)"

#. Tag: para
#: details-loans.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Making a 13th principal repayment every year. (This assumes a loan that is "
"repaid in monthly installments.)"
msgstr ""
"Vsako leto 13. odplačil glavnice. (To predvideva posojilo, ki se odplačuje v "
"mesečnih obrokih.)"

#. Tag: para
